The paper discusses the theoretical advantages of deep learning, specifically in terms of generalization and expressivity. These concepts are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper. Among them, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely as they directly relate to the main focus of the paper.
